Blackstone, Square Mile to Buy Mortgages From FDIC, WSJ Reports

-- B y   J e r a n   W i t t e n s t e i n
-- 
2011-03-16T22:37:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-16/blackstone-square-mile-to-buy-mortgages-from-fdic-wsj-reports.html
  Blackstone Group LP (BX)  and Square Mile
Capital LLC agreed to purchase a $385 million group of mortgages
from the U.S. Federal Deposit Insurance Corp., the Wall Street
Journal reported, citing unidentified people familiar with the
situation.  The mortgages are backed by 45 hotels and were held by the
failed Silverton bank in  Georgia , the newspaper said. Blackstone
and Square Mile will pay about 80 cents on the dollar for the
assets, according to the report.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jeran Wittenstein at 
 jwittenstei1@bloomberg.net  